         <div type="translation">
            <p>
               <supplied reason="lost" cert="low">The city</supplied> honoured with <supplied reason="lost">the finest and</supplied> fitting honours Zenon son of Menippos the son of Zenon the son of Kallias, father of Menippos and Zenon; high priest <supplied reason="subaudible">of the Imperial cult</supplied>, treasurer, temple-builder who had also filled all other offices and liturgies for his country zealously. He was admired for his self-restraint and proper behaviour and for his goodwill towards his country. Zenobios, fourth of the name from Epaphroditos oversaw <supplied reason="subaudible">provision of the monument</supplied>.</p>
         </div>
         <div type="commentary">
            <p>The sons of this man are honoured in very similar terms in two inscriptions (not yet published)</p>
            <p>For the epimelete see <ref type="inscription" n="1919" target="121020.xml"/>.</p>
